Speaking after President Cyril Ramaphosa's State of the Nation Address on Thursday night, DA leader Mmusi Maimane slammed the president's "conflicting" messages around Eskom. "We must take it in context. In February, the president spoke about unbundling Eskom. In June, he talks about giving it more money. Which is it exactly?" he asked in News24's studio. "What is more worrying, we're one of the last few countries who are not only heavily co-dependent, but we have this national grid without reform. We need deliberate reform."  WATCH: 'The President is a dreamer' - MP's react to Ramaphosa's address President Cyril Ramaphosa delivered his State of the Nation Address on Thursday in Parliament. Some members of parliament felt that the President is unrealistic in his plan to make South Africa better.  KEEP UPDATED on the latest news by subscribing to our FREE newsletter. - FOLLOW News24 on Twitter 